SLI (Slackel-Live installer) is a GUI to install or copy the live system (based on GTK+2).

Slackware-live is a dependency for SLI.

The SLKBUILD source package and binary can be found on http://www.slackel.gr/repo/source/slackel-source/slackware-live-installer-1.2.5/3/
To build the package fakeroor slkbuild -X
To install the package sudo spkg sli-1.2.5-x86_64-3dj.txz or sudo installpkg sli-1.2.5-x86_64-3dj.txz

If you want to build from the source in hrere in git:
SLI use the CMake construction system. So, cmake has to be installed if it is not ( sudo slapt-get -u && sudo slapt-get -i cmake)

The installation procedure is:
1) download the sources
git clone https://github.com/djemos/slackel-live-installer.git
2) cd slackel-live-installer
3) sh maketxz.sh
4) Install the package
sudo spkg sli-1.2.5-x86_64-3dj.txz or sudo installpkg sli-1.2.5-x86_64-3dj.txz
